<p>Oh, boy. I used to love Bop-Its, and this touched my nostalgic-creepy nerve in a very unexpected way.</p>
<p>What unsettled me more than a Bop-It communicating in a very Bop-Itty way was the looming expectation that at some point, it was <em>going</em> to break form and say something&#8230; <em>un-Bop-Itty</em>. I knew it was going to happen, and I was waiting nervously <em>for</em> it to happen.</p>
<p>When it happened, it did give me a little tingle, but it left me wanting more. I really like this, but it only feels like a quarter of a good meal, you know? Novote from me, but good job nonetheless!</p>

